Title: Mapping Hawking into Unruh Thermal Properties

Authors: S. Deser, Orit Levin

Comments: 10 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D59 (1999) 064004

By globally embedding curved spaces into higher dimensional flat ones, werelevant curved space detectors become Rindler ones, whose temperature andentropy reproduce the originals. Specific illustrations include Schwarzschild,Schwarzschild-(anti)deSitter, Reissner-Nordstrom and BTZ spaces.